==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bridewell
<hw>Bride"well</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A house of
correction for the confinement of disorderly persons; -- so called from
a hospital built in 1553 near <etsep>St. Bride's (<plain>or</plain>
Bridget's) well</etsep>, in London, which was subsequently a penal
workhouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bridge</ent>⟦br⟧
